===Etymology===
 First used by U.S. President Ronald Reagan to describe weak enemies fighting individually or in small, underground groups for their homeland in the Middle East, particularly Palestinians.  Previously, a guerilla, or revolutionary, engaged in guerilla warfare.

===Noun===
# Someone who uses terror as a weapon in a (usually violent) political struggle, typically in an attempt to coerce a more powerful opponent, such as a government.  Formerly, someone who governs by terror, as in "The Terror" of the French revolution.

